## The Rewriting Checklist

Before you ship content:

- [ ] Removed all buzzwords from the banned list
- [ ] No "discover," "unlock," "unleash," "essential," "evolve"
- [ ] No "in today's world" or "as technology evolves" openers
- [ ] No "At the end of the day" or "Bottom line" closers
- [ ] Active voice > 80% (subjects do actions)
- [ ] Contractions used naturally (don't, can't, it's, you're)
- [ ] No multiple adjectives in a row
- [ ] Numbers instead of vague words ("40% faster" not "significantly faster")
- [ ] Short paragraphs (max 3-4 sentences)
- [ ] Short sentences (average 15-20 words)
- [ ] No hedging ("arguably," "somewhat," "might")
- [ ] No repetition (say it once, clearly)
- [ ] No corporate jargon (leverage, synergy, paradigm)
- [ ] Read it aloud — does it sound like you talking?

If it sounds like a person wrote it, you're done.

